[src:yargs-cli/global-objects-array] This section provides some examples of common array operations in JavaScript.
[src:yargs-cli/global-objects-array] This example shows three ways to create new array: first using array literal notation, then using the `Array()` constructor, and finally using `String.prototype.split()` to build the array from a string.
