[src:yargs-cli/global-objects-array] This example shows two ways to check if the `fruits` array contains `"Banana"` and `"Cherry"`: first with the `includes()` method, and then with the `indexOf()` method to test for an index value that's not `-1`.
[src:yargs-cli/global-objects-array] This example uses the `push()` method to append a new string to the `fruits` array.
[src:yargs-cli/global-objects-array] This example uses the `pop()` method to remove the last item from the `fruits` array.
[src:yargs-cli/global-objects-array] This example uses the `splice()` method to remove the last 3 items from the `fruits` array.
